You think Facebook is the only one to worry about?

How

Facebook has a lot of information about you. It’s overwhelming figuring out what data the company has collected on you, let alone trying to do anything to curb it. With the passage of new General Data Protection Regulations (GDPR), if you are an EU citizen you can start demanding companies delete the data they have on you and request records of what they have collected.

This website walks you through how to download your Facebook data, upload the list of companies that have collaborated with Facebook to serve you targeted advertisements, and automatically send direct messages to the companies asking them to send the information they have on you and delete it. The site also provides a breakdown of the types of companies who have your information. We hope this empowers you to understand a little bit about data collection and provides a helpful solution to take control of your digital footprint in one corner of the internet.


Get Your Data

Step 1 & 2

1. Login to your facebook account
2. Click on your “Settings”

Step 3

3. In “Your Facebook Information” tab, under “Download your information”, click on “View”

Step 4

4. Change the download format to “JSON” and create file
